541 Q: A CloudWatch Events ____ matches incoming events and routes them to targets (EC2, Lambda, Kinesis, ECS, Step Functions, SQS, SNS) for processing.
541 A: rule

542 Q: T or F: Elasticache supports security groups.
542 A: T. "ElastiCache supports both subnet security groups in Amazon Virtual Private Cloud (Amazon VPC) and classic Amazon EC2 security groups." from https://d0.awsstatic.com/whitepapers/performance-at-scale-with-amazon-elasticache.pdf

543 Q: T or F: You can use consistent hashing with both Redis and Memcached.
543 A: F. Memcached only.

544 Q: Redis replication is (synchronous|asynchronous).
544 A: Asynchronous. You could lose some data if your primary node fails. Even if it automatically fails over and promotes a read replica as the new primary, that replica may not have all the data the original primary had. "If you have crucial data that cannot be lost (for example, transactional or purchase data), we recommend that you also store that in a durable database such as Amazon DynamoDB or Amazon RDS." https://d0.awsstatic.com/whitepapers/performance-at-scale-with-amazon-elasticache.pdf

545 Q: T or F: You can use a self-signed certificate for HTTPS communication between CloudFront and your origin.
