600 Q: What AWS service can discover your data on an AWS data service or any JDBC-compatible data source and stores the associated metadata in its own catalog?
600 A: AWS Glue

601 Q: The ____ ____ ____ allows the client to call a single Lambda function in the backend. The function accesses many resources or features of other AWS services, including calling other Lambda functions.
601 A: Lambda proxy integration. See https://docs.aws.amazon.com/apigateway/latest/developerguide/set-up-lambda-proxy-integrations.html

602 Q: A ____ ____ ____ enables you to integrate an API route with a Lambda function. When a client calls your API, API Gateway sends the request to the Lambda function and returns the function's response to the client.
602 A: Lambda proxy integration. See https://docs.aws.amazon.com/apigateway/latest/developerguide/http-api-develop-integrations-lambda.html

603 Q: What AWS service helps you manage your software licenses by creating licensing rules that get enforced when you launch an EC2.
603 A: AWS License Manager

604 Q: Which AWS services is a virtual appliance that works with VMWare vCenter and allows you to import your VMs as EC2s.
604 A: Amazon EC2 VM Import Connector

605 Q: T or F: VM Import/Export allows you to import a VM image as an EC2. 
605 A: T. You can import a VM image as either an EC2 or an AMI.

606 Q: T or F: VM Import/Export allows you to import a VM image as an AMI.
606 A: T. You can import a VM image as either an EC2 or an AMI.

607 Q: What are the 3 types of VMs you can migrate using Server Migration Service (SMS)?
607 A: VMWare, Azure, Hyper-V

608 Q: T or F: SMS is agentless.
608 A: T. CloudEndure requires an agent, though. Instead of an agent, SMS uses the Server Migration Connector (SMS Connector), a pre-configured VM you install in the same virtualization environment as your source VM (the one you want to replicate). When you do the replication, SMS Connector takes a snapshot of the VM, creates a VM image, uploads it to S3, and then VM Import/Export turns it into an EBS snapshot and creates an AMI. See https://aws.amazon.com/blogs/architecture/field-notes-choosing-a-rehost-migration-tool-cloudendure-or-aws-sms/

609 Q: T or F: a single CloudWatch Events rule can route to multiple targets.
609 A: T.

610 Q: T or F: Kinesis Video Streams can store video.
610 A: T.

611 Q: T or F: Kinesis Video Streams can output an HLS stream.
611 A: T. See https://aws.amazon.com/blogs/aws/amazon-kinesis-video-streams-adds-support-for-hls-output-streams/

612 Q: T or F: An ALB has a security group
612 A: T

613 Q: T or F: An NLB has a security group.
613 A: F

614 Q: What is the minimum visibility timeout for a message in SQS?
614 A: 0 seconds minimum and 12 hours maximum.

615 Q: What is the maximum visibility timeout for a message in SQS?
615 A: 0 seconds minimum and 12 hours maximum.

616 Q: T or F: You can only assign one security group to an instance.
616 A: F. You can assign up to five security groups to an instance.

617 Q: T or F: You can assign up to five security groups to an instance.
617 A: T

618 Q: T or F: re: EC2, There is a vCPU-based on-demand instance limit per region.
618 A: T.

619 Q: Which is better for storing session data, RDS or DynamoDB?
619 A: DynamoDB. It's more performant.

620 Q: T or F: Amazon Athena supports XML.
620 A: F. It supports Apache Parquet, Apache ORC, and JSON.

621 Q: T or F: Elasticache Memcached supports encryption.
621 A: F. Elasticache Redis supports encryption at rest and in transit.

622 Q: T or F: Elasticache Redis supports encryption.
622 A: T. Elasticache Redis supports encryption at rest and in transit. Elasticache Memcached does not.

623 Q: T or F: NAT Gateway supports both IPv4 and IPv6.
623 A: F. IPv4 only. For IPv6, use an Egress-Only Internet Gateway

624 Q: T or F: Route 53 geolocation routing requires a default route.
624 A: T. Route 53 will use this route if the location of the requesting client can't be determined.

625 Q: T or F: After you create a set of DHCP options, you can't modify them.
625 A: T. See https://docs.aws.amazon.com/vpc/latest/userguide/VPC_DHCP_Options.html

626 Q: T or F: You can have multiple sets of DHCP options, but you can associate only one set of DHCP options with a VPC at a time.
626 A: T. "After you associate a new set of DHCP options with a VPC, any existing instances and all new instances that you launch in the VPC use the new options. You don't need to restart or relaunch the instances." See https://docs.aws.amazon.com/vpc/latest/userguide/VPC_DHCP_Options.html

627 Q: Defining a ____ ____ instead of a ____ ____ allows you to have multiple versions.
627 A: launch template, launch configuration

628 Q: By using a [launch template|launch configuration], you can create an ASG that launches both spot and on-demand instances.
628 A: launch template. See https://docs.aws.amazon.com/autoscaling/ec2/userguide/LaunchTemplates.html

629 Q: By using a [launch template|launch configuration], you can create an ASG that launches multiple instance types.
629 A: launch template. See https://docs.aws.amazon.com/autoscaling/ec2/userguide/LaunchTemplates.html

630 Q: AWS enforces quotas on the number of EC2s you can run based on their ____.
630 A: vCPUs.

631 Q: "____ ____ is a fully managed data security and data privacy service that uses machine learning and pattern matching to discover and protect your sensitive data in AWS."
631 A: Amazon Macie. See https://aws.amazon.com/macie/faq/ and https://aws.amazon.com/macie/

632 Q: What data store(s) does Amazon Macie search?
632 A: S3 only

633 Q: RDS read replicas are updated [synchronously|asynchronously].
633 A: asynchronously

634 Q: T or F: RDS read replicas for MySQL, MariaDB, PostgreSQL, Oracle, and SQL Server can be encrypted.
634 A: T. You can optionally use KMS to encrypt the data at rest. It's also encrypted in transit from the master to the replica.

635 Q: "____ scaling creates target tracking scaling policies for the resources in your scaling plan."
635 A: Dynamic. "These scaling policies adjust resource capacity in response to live changes in resource utilization. The intention is to provide enough capacity to maintain utilization at the target value specified by the scaling strategy." from https://docs.aws.amazon.com/autoscaling/plans/userguide/how-it-works.html

636 Q: "____ scaling uses machine learning to analyze each resource's historical workload and regularly forecasts the future load for the next two days."
636 A: Predictive. "Predictive scaling generates scheduled scaling actions to make sure that the resource capacity is available before your application needs it. Like dynamic scaling, predictive scaling works to maintain utilization at the target value specified by the scaling strategy." from https://docs.aws.amazon.com/autoscaling/plans/userguide/how-it-works.html

637 Q: Re: RDS: "A ____ ____ acts as a container for engine configuration values that are applied to one or more DB instances."
637 A: parameter group. See https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AmazonRDS/latest/UserGuide/USER_WorkingWithParamGroups.html

638 Q: T or F: SQS supports KMS encryption.
638 A: T. You can optionally configure any queue to use KMS.

639 Q: What is the default duration an SQS message is stored?
639 A: 4 days

640 Q: What is the max duration an SQS message can be stored?
640 A: 14 days

641 Q: re: SWF: "The ____ is a program that controls the coordination of tasks, i.e. their ordering, concurrency, and scheduling according to the application logic."
641 A: decider. SWF uses workers and a decider. See https://aws.amazon.com/swf/faqs/

642 Q: re: SWF: "____ are programs that interact with Amazon SWF to get tasks, process received tasks, and return the results."
642 A: workers. SWF uses workers and a decider. See https://aws.amazon.com/swf/faqs/

643 Q: How do workers and deciders get task information from the SWF service?
643 A: Polling. More specifically: long polling.

644 Q: "When an instance launches, Amazon EC2 Auto Scaling uses the value of the ____ for the Auto Scaling group to determine how long to wait before checking the health status of the instance."
644 A: HealthCheckGracePeriod. See https://docs.aws.amazon.com/autoscaling/ec2/userguide/healthcheck.html

645 Q: "A scaling ____ helps you prevent your Auto Scaling group from launching or terminating additional instances before the effects of previous activities are visible."
645 A: cooldown. See https://docs.aws.amazon.com/autoscaling/ec2/userguide/Cooldown.html

646 Q: T or F: You can't modify a launch configuration after you've created it.
646 A: T. See https://docs.aws.amazon.com/autoscaling/ec2/userguide/change-launch-config.html

647 Q: ____ define the port and protocol clients will use to reach an ALB.
647 A: Listeners

648 Q: ____ ____ are logical collections of AWS resources behind a load balancer.
648 A: Target groups. They can hold containers, IP addresses, or EC2 instances. Target groups are homogeneous and can't contain a mixture of these different types of resources; everything in the target group must be the same type of resource.

649 Q: What protocol does EFS use?
649 A: NFS. You can't use EFS with Windows instances.

650 Q: T or F: Multiple Amazon EC2 instances can access an Amazon EFS file system at the same time
650 A: T. "Amazon EFS file systems can be mounted on up to thousands of Amazon EC2 instances concurrently." https://docs.aws.amazon.com/efs/latest/ug/performance-tips.html

651 Q: T or F: EFS has multiple storage classes.
651 A: T. Standard and Infrequent Access. See https://docs.aws.amazon.com/efs/latest/ug/storage-classes.html

652 Q: What are the 2 throughput modes EFS uses?
652 A: Provisioned Throughput and Bursting Throughput. With bursting, your throughput increases as you use more storage. "Using the default Bursting Throughput mode, throughput scales as your file system grows. Using Provisioned Throughput mode, you can specify the throughput of your file system independent of the amount of data stored." See https://docs.aws.amazon.com/efs/latest/ug/performance.html.

653 Q: T or F: You can't use EFS with Windows instances.
653 A: T.

654 Q: T or F: You can access a single EFS share from instances in multiple AZs.
654 A: T.

655 Q: T or F: You can access EFS over DX or VPN from an on-prem client.
655 A: T. "You can mount your Amazon EFS file systems on your on-premises data center servers when connected to your Amazon VPC with AWS Direct Connect or AWS VPN." See https://docs.aws.amazon.com/efs/latest/ug/how-it-works.html

656 Q: T or F: An Amazon EFS file system can only have mount targets in one VPC at a time.
656 A: T. See https://docs.aws.amazon.com/efs/latest/ug/how-it-works.html

657 Q: T or F: You can mount an EFS file system using either the DNS name or the IP address of a mount target.
657 A: T. It'll have the same DNS name in all availability zones, but a different IP. So mounting using the IP is probably higher maintenance. "A mount target provides an IP address for an NFSv4 endpoint at which you can mount an Amazon EFS file system. You mount your file system using its Domain Name Service (DNS) name, which resolves to the IP address of the EFS mount target in the same Availability Zone as your EC2 instance." See https://docs.aws.amazon.com/efs/latest/ug/how-it-works.html BUT if you're mounting the filesystem from an on-prem host, you should use the IP address an  NOT the hostname: "For the sake of simplicity, we recommend mounting an Amazon EFS file system on an on-premises server using a mount target IP address instead of a DNS name." ibid

658 Q: How many mount targets can an EFS file system have in an availability zone?
658 A: 1.

659 Q: T or F: An Amazon EFS file system can only have mount targets in one VPC at a time.
659 A: T.

660 Q: What port does NFS use?
660 A: 2049

661 Q: ____ ____ is a fully managed backup service that makes it easy to centralize and automate data backup across AWS services in the cloud and on-premises.
661 A: AWS Backup. "AWS Backup is a unified backup service designed to simplify the creation, migration, restoration, and deletion of backups, while providing improved reporting and auditing." https://docs.aws.amazon.com/efs/latest/ug/efs-backup-solutions.html

662 Q: T or F: You can configure EFS to automatically move stale data to the IA storage class.
662 A: T. "Amazon EFS lifecycle management automatically manages cost-effective file storage for your file systems. When enabled, lifecycle management migrates files that haven't been accessed for a set period of time to the Infrequent Access (IA) storage class. You define that period of time by using a lifecycle policy." https://docs.aws.amazon.com/efs/latest/ug/how-it-works.html

663 Q: What are the 2 EFS performance modes?
663 A: General Purpose and Max I/O

664 Q: T or F: You can use DataSync to transfer files between two EFS file systems.
664 A: T

665 Q: ____ ____ is an online data transfer service that simplifies, automates, and accelerates copying large amounts of data to and from AWS storage services over the internet or AWS Direct Connect.
665 A: AWS DataSync. "DataSync includes encryption and integrity validation to help make sure your data arrives securely, intact, and ready to use." See https://aws.amazon.com/datasync/faqs/

666 Q: T or F: You can use AWS DataSync to copy files between EFS file systems in different regions.
666 A: T. "Yes, you can use AWS DataSync to transfer files between two EFS file systems, including ones in different AWS Regions or ones belonging to different AWS accounts." https://aws.amazon.com/efs/faq/

667 Q: T or F: You can access EFS from ECS.
667 A: T. ECS on EC2 or Fargate.

668 Q: T or F: You can access EFS from EKS.
668 A: T. EKS on EC2 or Fargate.

669 Q: T or F: You can access EFS from Lambda.
669 A: T.

670 Q: You can see the amount of memory used by a Lambda function by looking at (CloudWatch Logs|CloudWatch Metrics)?
670 A: Logs

671 Q: You can see the amount of memory provisioned for a Lambda function by looking at (CloudWatch Logs|CloudWatch Metrics)?
671 A: Logs

672 Q: What are the 2 types of targets a Lambda function can use for its DLQ?
672 A: SQS, SNS. See https://docs.aws.amazon.com/lambda/latest/dg/invocation-async.html#dlq

673 Q: Do you enable route propagation on a VGW or a CGW?
673 A: VGW.

674 Q: re: CloudFormation...use the ____ attribute when you want to wait on resource configuration actions before stack creation proceeds.
674 A: CreationPolicy. See https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AWSCloudFormation/latest/UserGuide/aws-attribute-creationpolicy.html Compare this to wait conditions: "For Amazon EC2 and Auto Scaling resources, we recommend that you use a CreationPolicy attribute instead of wait conditions." ... and wait conditions are best for coordinating the creation of stack resources with configuration actions external to the stack. See https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AWSCloudFormation/latest/UserGuide/aws-properties-waitcondition.html

675 Q: Which CloudFormation intrinsic function returns an array that lists Availability Zones for a specified region in alaphabetical order. 
675 A: Fn:GetAZs. YAML: "Fn::GetAZs: us-east-2"

676 Q: T or F: re: CloudFormation, you can use intrinsic functions only in specific parts of a template.
676 A: T. "Currently, you can use intrinsic functions in resource properties, outputs, metadata attributes, and update policy attributes. You can also use intrinsic functions to conditionally create stack resources." see https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AWSCloudFormation/latest/UserGuide/intrinsic-function-reference.html

677 Q: T or F: You can configure VPC security groups via AWS Firewall Manager.
677 A: T

678 Q: T or F: You can configure NACLs via AWS Firewall Manager.
678 A: F

697 Q: If I'm using CloudFront and my origin is in my own data center, I (can|cannot) use Direct Connect to transfer the objects stored in my own data center.
697 A: Can

698 Q: ____ ____ ____ are a way for customers to order and manage multiple direct connect ports as a single larger connection instead of as separate discrete connections.
698 A: Link Aggregation Groups (LAGs)

699 Q: All LAG connections must be dedicated connections and have a port speed of ____ Gbps or ____ Gbps.
699 A: 1 or 10. You can't mix 1Gbps and 10Gbps connections in the same LAG.

700 Q: T or F: You can use a LAG with a Direct Connect Dedicated Connection.
700 A: T. But not a Hosted Connection

701 Q: T or F: You can use a LAG with a Direct Connect Hosted Connection.
701 A: F. Only a Dedicated Connection

702 Q: You can have a maximum of ____ connections in a LAG.
702 A: 4

703 Q: ____ ____ ____ is a grouping of virtual private gateways (VGWs) and private virtual interfaces (VIFs).
703 A: Direct Connect gateway (DX Gateway)

704 Q: T or F: AWS Managed VPN service does not support Jumbo Frames.
704 A: T. It does not.

705 Q: T or F: Transit VIFs support jumbo frames
705 A: T.

706 Q: What AWS service provides static IP addresses that provide a fixed entry point to your applications and eliminate the complexity of managing specific IP addresses for different AWS Regions and Availability Zones?
706 A: AWS Global Accelerator

707 Q: What does an Elastic Network Adapter provide?
707 A: Enhanced networking for an EC2. Can also be done with an Intel 82599 VF interface

708 Q: T or F: You must specify subnets from at least two Availability Zones when you create an ALB.
708 A: T

709 Q: T or F: Each ALB target group can be associated with only one load balancer.
709 A: T

710 Q: T or F: You can use security groups with ALBs.
710 A: T.

711 Q: T or F: With Application Load Balancers, cross-zone load balancing is always enabled.
711 A: T. See https://docs.aws.amazon.com/elasticloadbalancing/latest/userguide/how-elastic-load-balancing-works.html#cross-zone-load-balancing

712 Q: T or F: With Network Load Balancers, cross-zone load balancing is disabled by default.
712 A: T. You can enable and disable it as you need.

713 Q: T or F: You can assign an Elastic IP to an NLB.
713 A: T.

714 Q: T or F: Targets behind an ELB need public IP addresses.
714 A: F. "Both internet-facing and internal load balancers route requests to your targets using private IP addresses. Therefore, your targets do not need public IP addresses to receive requests from an internal or an internet-facing load balancer." from https://docs.aws.amazon.com/elasticloadbalancing/latest/userguide/how-elastic-load-balancing-works.html

715 Q: T or F: DX Gateway enables you to interface with VPCs in any AWS Region.
715 A: T

716 Q: T or F: DX Gateway enables you to use a single Private VIF to interface w/multiple VPCs.
716 A: T. See https://aws.amazon.com/directconnect/faqs/

717 Q: T or F: DX Gateway enables you to use a single Transit VIF to interface w/multiple Transit Gateways.
717 A: T. Up to 3 Transit Gateways. See https://aws.amazon.com/directconnect/faqs/

718 Q: What types of VIFs can you attach to the VPC-end of a DX?
718 A: Private VIF, Public VIF, Transit VIF.

719 Q: What AWS service collects findings from the security services enabled across your AWS accounts: Amazon GuardDuty (intrusion), Amazon Inspector (vulnerability scans), and Amazon Macie (PII)
719 A: Security Hub

720 Q: T or F: Cognito Identity Pools store user profiles.
720 A: F. Cognito User Pools store user profiles. A User Pool is your user directory.

721 Q: What is the storage limit of RDS MySQL?
721 A: 6 TB

722 Q: What is the storage limit of RDS MariaDB?
722 A: 6 TB

723 Q: What is the storage limit of RDS Oracle?
723 A: 6 TB

724 Q: What is the storage limit of RDS PostgreSQL?
724 A: 6 TB

725 Q: What is the storage limit of RDS SQL Server?
725 A: 4 TB

726 Q: What is the storage limit of RDS Aurora?
726 A: 64 TB

727 Q: T or F: You can't use jumbo frames on VPN connections or traffic sent over an Internet gateway.
727 A: T. VPN connections and traffic sent over an Internet gateway cannot support jumbo frames.

728 Q: T or F: You can use jumbo frames for traffic between your VPCs and your on-premises networks over AWS Direct Connect.
728 A: T. See https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AWSEC2/latest/UserGuide/network_mtu.html

729 Q: What RAID levels does EBS support?
729 A: 0, 1, and 10

730 Q: What is the max size of an SNS message?
730 A: 256 KB

731 Q: T or F: You can subscribe an SQS standard or FIFO queue to an SNS topic.
731 A: F. SNS does not support forwarding messages to SQS FIFO queues. You can use SNS to forward messages to standard queues.

732 Q: What is the minimum amount of RAM you can assign to a Lambda function?
732 A: 128 MB

733 Q: What is the maximum amount of RAM you can assign to a Lambda function?
733 A: 3 GB

734 Q: To use read replicas with RDS MySQL, you have to use with storage engine?
734 A: InnoDB. Not MyISAM

735 Q: If your AWS Batch job has insufficient permissions to run, your job will be stuck in the ____ state.
735 A: RUNNABLE

736 Q: If AWS can't provision the CPU and RAM you requested for your AWS Batch job, your job will be stuck in the ____ state.
736 A: RUNNABLE

737 Q: If your AWS Batch job can't run due to EC2 limits on your account, it  will be stuck in the ____ state.
737 A: RUNNABLE

738 Q: T or F: By default, IAM users can't access the Billing and Cost Management Console.
738 A: T. That access has to be explicitly activate by the account owner, and then proper IAM permissions must be given to users. "By default, IAM users do not have access to the AWS Billing and Cost Management console. You or your account administrator must grant users access. You can do this by activating IAM user access to the Billing and Cost Management console and attaching an IAM policy to your users." see https://docs.aws.amazon.com/awsaccountbilling/latest/aboutv2/control-access-billing.html

739 Q: What is the sequence of fields in a cron expression?
739 A: Minute, hour, day of month, month, day of week
# ┌───────────── minute (0 - 59)
# │ ┌───────────── hour (0 - 23)
# │ │ ┌───────────── day of the month (1 - 31)
# │ │ │ ┌───────────── month (1 - 12)
# │ │ │ │ ┌───────────── day of the week (0 - 6) (Sunday to Saturday;
# │ │ │ │ │                                   7 is also Sunday on some systems)
# │ │ │ │ │
# │ │ │ │ │
# * * * * * <command to execute>

740 Q: T or F: When you create an OpsWorks Stack, all its resources must be in the same region.
740 A: T. An OpsWorks Stack can only control resources within its region. An OpsWorks Stack can be cloned, but only within the region.

741 Q: T or F: You can clone an OpsWorks Stack.
741 A: T. But only within its region; you can't create a clone into a new region.

742 Q: T or F: Without a Stack Policy, all resources in a CloudFormation stack can be updated by anyone with permission to update the stack.
742 A: T. "When you create a stack, all update actions are allowed on all resources. By default, anyone with stack update permissions can update all of the resources in the stack." See https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AWSCloudFormation/latest/UserGuide/protect-stack-resources.html

743 Q: You can prevent stack resources from being unintentionally updated or deleted during a stack update by using a ____ ____.
743 A: Stack policy. See https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AWSCloudFormation/latest/UserGuide/protect-stack-resources.html

744 Q: After you set a ____ ____, all of the resources in the stack are protected by default.
744 A: Stack policy. "To allow updates on specific resources, you specify an explicit Allow statement for those resources in your stack policy. You can define only one stack policy per stack, but, you can protect multiple resources within a single policy. A stack policy applies to all AWS CloudFormation users who attempt to update the stack. You can't associate different stack policies with different users." from https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AWSCloudFormation/latest/UserGuide/protect-stack-resources.html

745 Q: A CloudFormation Stack Policy can be removed using the CLI.
745 A: F. You can't remove a Stack Policy once it's created. You can update it, and you have to do that via the CLI.

746 Q: A CloudFormation Stack Policy can be updated using the CLI.
746 A: T. It can't be removed and it can't be updated using the console.

747 Q: T or F: You change the instance type of an EBS-backed instance when the instance is stopped.
747 A: T. But not while it's running. You can also change its kernel and user data. See https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AWSEC2/latest/UserGuide/ComponentsAMIs.html#storage-for-the-root-device

748 Q: T or F: You can change the size of an EBS volume—even the root device—that's attached to a running instance.
748 A: T. 

749 Q: What 2 STS APIs could a custom identity broker application use?
749 A: AssumeRole, GetFederationToken

750 Q: What type of federation would you use to integrate Active Directory with AWS?
750 A: SAML 2.0 federation. AD is the most common but not the only SAML 2.0 compatible IdP

751 Q: Instead of using the STS:AssumeRoleWithWebIdentity API, AWS recommends that you use what?
751 A: Cognito. It allows anonymous users, data syncrhonization, and MFA.

752 Q: Instead of using a token vending machine, AWS recommends that you use what?
752 A: Cognito. 

753 Q: A service catalog Launch Constraint (or Launch Role) is required when you add a product to the service catalog.
753 A: F. Launch Constraint is optional. Without it, users who launch the product must have IAM permissions for CloudFormation and all resources and actions named in the product's template.

754 Q: T or F: When you buy a regional reserved instance, you reserve computing capacity in the designated region.
754 A: F. "A regional Reserved Instance does not reserve capacity." But a zonal RI does reserve capacity within the AZ where it's purchased. See https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AWSEC2/latest/UserGuide/reserved-instances-scope.html

755 Q: T or F: When you buy a zonal reserved instance, you reserve computing capacity in the designated AZ.
755 A: T. "A zonal Reserved Instance reserves capacity in the specified Availability Zone." But a regional RI does not reserve capacity within its region. See https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AWSEC2/latest/UserGuide/reserved-instances-scope.html

756 Q: T or F: A regional RI allows you to launch instances of different sizes.
756 A: T. As long as they're within the same family. "The Reserved Instance discount applies to instance usage within the instance family, regardless of size. Only supported on Amazon Linux/Unix Reserved Instances with default tenancy." See https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AWSEC2/latest/UserGuide/reserved-instances-scope.html

757 Q: T or F: A zonal RI allows you to launch instances of different sizes.
757 A: F. Zonal reserved instances do not have instance size flexibility. Regional RIs do. See https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AWSEC2/latest/UserGuide/reserved-instances-scope.html

758 Q: What AWS service would you use if you want to build a chatbot?
758 A: Amazon Lex. Lex uses voice and text.

759 Q: What AWS service do you use for text to speech?
759 A: Amazon Polly

760 Q: T or F: SimpleAD supports MFA.
760 A: F

761 Q: If an SCP is present, it implicitly (allows|denies) all actions.
761 A: Denies. It has to contain Effect:Allow statements in order to do anything. Blacklist = start by allowing *, then deny specific actions. Whitelist = Just include Effect:Allow for the actions you want to allow (since everything else is already implicitly denied).761 Q: If an SCP is present, it implicitly (allows|denies) all actions.

762 Q: An account in an AWS Organization can receive RI discounts on any instances it uses that match any reservations purchased by (the root account|any other account).
762 A: Any other account. But the master account can disable RI discount sharing between accounts.

763 Q: T or F: An SCP can have multiple Statement elements.
763 A: F. But you can have multiple objects in a single Statement elements. Every SCP should have one and only one Statement elements.

764 Q: T or F: Systems Manager Parameter Store can hold encrypted strings.
764 A: T. "You can encrypt your sensitive data using your own AWS Key Management Service (KMS) key or your user account default key provided by AWS KMS." From https://aws.amazon.com/systems-manager/faq/

765 Q: T or F: If you're performing a homogenous migration from MySQL to Amazon RDS MySQL or Amazon Aurora MySQL, you should always use DMS.
765 A: F. "If you're performing a homogeneous migration, use your engine’s native tools (such as MySQL dump or MySQL replication) whenever possible." See https://aws.amazon.com/premiumsupport/knowledge-center/migrate-mysql-rds-dms/ BUT if you need availability during the migration, you should use DMS.

766 Q: T or F: Lambda reads events from Kinesis Data Streams.
766 A: T. DynamoDB, Kinesis Data Streams, Kafka, SQSa

767 Q: T or F: Lambda reads events from DynamoDB.
767 A: T. DynamoDB, Kinesis Data Streams, Kafka, SQS

768 Q: T or F: Lambda reads events from Kafka.
768 A: T. DynamoDB, Kinesis Data Streams, Kafka, SQS

769 Q: T or F: Lambda reads events from SQS.
769 A: T. DynamoDB, Kinesis Data Streams, Kafka, SQS

770 Q: T or F: KDF can trigger a Lambda function to transform the data in its stream.
770 A: T. See https://docs.aws.amazon.com/firehose/latest/dev/data-transformation.html

771 Q: How long does it take to transfer 1 TB over a 100 Mbps connection?
771 A: One day. (1 day and 41 minutes. See https://www.expedient.com/knowledgebase/tools-and-calculators/file-transfer-time-calculator/)

772 Q: T or F: You can expand the size of an EBS root volume from the console.
772 A: T. And the CLI (aws ec2 modify-volume). You don't have to detach the volume first.

773 Q: T or F: You can expand the size of an EBS root volume from the CLI.
773 A: T. Using aws ec2 modify-volume. Also from the console. You don't have to detach the volume first.

774 Q: T or F: You can access S3 via HTTPS only.
774 A: F. S3 exposes HTTP and HTTPS endpoints.

775 Q: T or F: S3 access logs are delivered in real time.
775 A: F. Might take hours to deliver. S3 event notifications are faster.


